main.name: Colin Dale
main.bio: Hi there, I am Colin!  My passion is working with businesses to help build and scale their companies with the use of Web Apps.  At the beginning of 2018 I starting using ReactJS to build fully functional responsive web applications and since then I have built many projects that I am proud of! Be sure to check out my most recent build, Web3 Lottery App made with Next, TailwindCSS and ThirdWeb.  I am passionate about learning and implementing new technologies that help me grow my skill set as a Developer. My new found love is Next-App using Typescript and TailwindCSS to for styling.  Currently I am a Success Coach for Papa Fam, an online coding community where we build clones of existing apps like Facebook, Twitter, Medium and many more! Being a part of this amazing community has been essential to my coding journey. I help students learn to code and help answer any questions within the community.  It’s exciting to watch upcoming developers hone their craft through my coaching.  I am looking for a position in Web Development that will utilize my react skills and help move your business forward.  I would love to meet you!   Please contact me at the phone number, email address below or fill out my contact form at the bottom  .

education.description: I learned HTML, CSS, JavaScript, ReactJs, Typescript, and React Native programming

work.title: Arduino(CPP) micro-controller programmer/Low-voltage Electronics
work.description: Assisting in design process of building guitar junction-boxes. My role includes programming microcontrollers for the junction's pcbs, building cables and fulfilling online orders.

work.title: Success Coach
work.description: I help students with anything that is covered in a basic coding bootcamp one on one. I also do coaching calls with a large group, where I have covered various ReactJs and NextJs Topics.
